b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48487.htm)  [Next](sbe48489.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n41\\. Nor the (expiatory performance) described in the chapter treating of\nqualification; that being impossible on account of the Sm _ri_ ti referring to\nsuch lapse.\n\nThose expiatory performances which are described in the chapter treating of\nqualification (Pu. Mi. Su. VI) are not possible in the case of him who has\nlapsed from the condition of a Naish _th_ ika; since such expiations do not\napply to him, as is shown by a Sm _ri_ ti text referring to such lapse, viz.\n'He who having once entered on the duties of a Naish _th_ ika lapses from\nthem, for such a slayer of the Self I do not see any expiatory work by which\nhe might become clean.' The expiatory ceremony referred to in the Purva Mima\n_m_ sa therefore applies to the case of other Brahma _k_ arins only.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 42. A minor one, thus some; and hence they hold the existence of\nexpiation, as in the case of eating.](sbe48489.htm)\n\n"